 2 \int_0^{y/2} e^{-(x+y)} \, \mathrm{d} x = 2 \int_0^{y/2} e^{-x} e^{-y} \, \mathrm{d} x = 2e^{-y} \int_0^{y/2} e^{-x} \, \mathrm{d} x = 2 e^{-y} \left[ e^{-x} \right]_0^{y/2} = 2 e^{-y}\left( e^{-y/2} - 1 \right) \\ = 2e^{-y-y/2} - e^{-y} 
 P(2X \le Y) = \int_0^\infty \int_{2x}^\infty 2 e^{-(x+y)} \, \mathrm{d} y \, \mathrm{d} x  = 2 \int_0^\infty e^{-x} \left( \int_{2x}^\infty e^{-y} \, \mathrm{d} y \right) \, \mathrm{d} x \\ = 2 \int_0^\infty e^{-x}e^{-2x} \, \mathrm{d} x = 2 \int_0^\infty e^{-3x} \, \mathrm{d}x = \frac{2}{3} 
